			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: One of the largest PVP battles to date...
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1788741">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							/shrug,<br />
<br />
I quit EvE before they really got Time-Dilation working, so the largest fleet battles I saw were 1200-1600, but I saw quite a few of those, including participating in the deaths of over 5 titans, at a time when titan's were rather rarer then they are today in game.  (Each titan is ~50-100 Billion isk, which is a few thousand RL dollars).<br />
<br />
Voice comm discipline is an absolute must, to the point that one of the 'spy games' that can be played is logging into the enemy's TS and just blabbering at critical moments.<br />
<br />
The thing with EvE was/is that there are multi-hundred+ engagements that have a specific set of builds and require specific behavior (like TS discipline), and there are 5-100 person 'roams' that have entirely different builds and usually require different behaviors.<br />
<br />
The average EvE player age is older then any other MMO (that I know of), and more importantly, the EvE population is divided into 2 groups, with the 'Empire-based players' being younger on average then the 0.0-based players.  And these battles are part of 0.0 life.<br />
<br />
EvE is basically MMO in &quot;Elite-Hardcore-Raid&quot; style.  On a scale that's actually difficult to explain, but here's an attempt.<br />
In EvE, system control is gained by controlling moons in a system using 'mini-space stations' known as POSes.  Each POS requires fuel, and most POSes must be refueled ~once a week or so.<br />
Now imagine having anywhere from 10 to 100 POSes in a system, and owning 100 systems.  Imagine the time-sink that is POS refueling. <br />
Now, quite a few of those POSes are used for another purpose (be in 'mining', production of new ships/equipment, etc.).  The POSes must be supplied, or drained of supplies daily-weekly.  How much time do you think that is?<br />
Especially when the only ship that can do it effeciently is a Jump Freighter, at the cost of 5 billion isk (a few hundred RL dollars), that has no guns, but has a big enough cargo to be able to move the fuel/products around.<br />
<br />
Now imagine that there is a 100 other things like that.<br />
<br />
Very little in the EvE universe is NOT made by players.  Literally.  Those 100 billion isk ships are made using minerals that have to be mined (or harvested from the wreaks of ships!).  They require soo many minerals that you have to use freighters (Multiple) to move the components around, let alone the 3 MONTHS of RL time required for the titan to be constructed once you've gotten everything in place.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer">&quot;We live in a society absolutely dependent on science and technology and yet have cleverly arranged things so that almost no one understands science and technology. That's a clear prescription for disaster.&quot; <br />
-Carl Sagan</div></blockquote>
				
                                        
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
